                    <h1>How To Arrange Step By Step ?</h1>
                    <p>
                        Divide:

                        Recursively split the unsorted list into two halves of approximately equal size until each sublist contains only a single element (which is inherently sorted).
                        Conquer:

                        Base case: If a sublist contains only one element, it's already sorted.
                        Recursively merge sort each sublist.
                        Combine (Merge):

                        Repeatedly merge pairs of sorted sublists back into larger, sorted lists.
                        To merge two sorted sublists:
                        Create a temporary empty list to hold the merged result.
                        Compare the first elements of each sublist.
                        Append the smaller element to the temporary list and remove it from its original sublist.
                        Repeat this process until one sublist is empty.
                        Append any remaining elements from the non-empty sublist to the temporary list.
                        Replace the original sublists with the merged temporary list.
                    </p>

